<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="31">
This genus has several diagnostic characters that clearly separate it from all other Neotropical 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="20" pageNumber="31" rank="tribe" tribe="Clytrini">Clytrini</taxonomicName>
: scutellum inclined posterodorsally, distinctly protruding from the plane of elytra; intercoxal prosternal process nearly absent between fore coxae; epipleural margin broadly angled, tip rounded; elytra without pubescence; frons with medial pit, densely and coarsely punctate throughout; pygidium strongly convex; pronotum with lateral margins sulcate to receive antennae in repose; dorsum brilliant metallic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
